課程概述 Course Description
       The purpose of this course is to provide EMBA students with an advanced exploration of the contemporary important topics in accounting and finance for today’s business enterprises and capital markets. Through comprehensive case studies, students will develop the practical research application skills necessary to analyze and make corporate decisions regarding accounting and finance in for-profit and not-for-profit companies. In addition, the recently developed corporate social responsibility and integrated reporting concepts and real cases will also be introduced. The purpose of this course is to provide EMBA students with an advanced exploration of the contemporary important topics in accounting and finance for today’s business enterprises and capital markets. Through comprehensive case studies, students will develop the practical research application skills necessary to analyze and make corporate decisions regarding accounting and finance in for-profit and not-for-profit companies. In addition, the recently developed corporate social responsibility and integrated reporting concepts and real cases will also be introduced.     

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
Facilitate EMBA students’ understanding of issues in accounting and finance.Introduce students to the professional ethics in the corporate activities.Develop students’ global perspectives in the current business environment. 

