財務與會計專題                          


  	The purpose of this course is to provide EMBA students with an advanced exploration of the contemporary important topics in accounting and finance for today’s business enterprises and capital markets. Through comprehensive case studies, students will develop the practical research application skills necessary to analyze and make corporate decisions regarding accounting and finance in for-profit and not-for-profit companies. In addition, the recently developed corporate social responsibility and integrated reporting concepts and real cases will also be introduced. 

